abstract_ssm: Edwin Rolfe - born Solomon Fishman - (1910-1954) was a journalist, author, and Communist Party activist. In 1937, Rolfe went to Spain to cover the Spanish Civil War for the Volunteer for Libertyand the Daily Worker. The images in this collection were accrued by Rolfe in the course of his work as a journalist in Spain. The collection contains images of British author and assistant commissar of the Fifteenth International Brigade Ralph Bates and African-American author Langston Hughes as well as barricades, bombed/shelled buildings, medical personnel and street scenes
